Source-derived content
----------------------

The exact 14 pCAT item statements, original CFIR mappings, response structure,
and source-table strategy prompts in these files are reproduced or adapted
from Robinson and Damschroder (2023):

* inst/extdata/pcat_items.csv
* inst/extdata/pcat_cfir_mappings.csv (rows labelled "original")
* inst/extdata/pcat_eric_candidates.csv
* inst/extdata/pcat_long_template.csv and pcat_wide_template.csv, to the extent
  that they reproduce item wording or response fields

Robinson CH, Damschroder LJ. A pragmatic context assessment tool (pCAT): using
a Think Aloud method to develop an assessment of contextual barriers to
change. Implementation Science Communications. 2023;4:3.
https://doi.org/10.1186/s43058-022-00380-5

The article and its supplementary materials are licensed under the Creative
Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0):
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

Adaptations include transcription into machine-readable CSV files,
standardized field and construct names, stable item identifiers, normalized
response codes, and software-derived classification, summary, visualization,
and reporting fields. The item statements were transcribed without intentional
wording changes; CSV quoting and whitespace are formatting changes.

The updated CFIR mapping fields in inst/extdata/pcat_items.csv and the rows
labelled "2022" in inst/extdata/pcat_cfir_mappings.csv are adapted from the
article main text and Supplementary Table S3 of Domlyn et al. (2026):

Domlyn AM, Dodge J, Pfeiffer PN, Robinson CH, Evans L, Damschroder LJ, Stewart
MA, Garlick B, Sussman JB, Nevedal AL. Evaluating the utility of an abbreviated
Consolidated Framework for Implementation Research (CFIR) for rapid qualitative
analysis: a suicide prevention program case study. Implementation Science
Communications. 2026;7:129.
https://doi.org/10.1186/s43058-026-00956-5

The source articles' CC BY 4.0 terms apply to the source-derived content. The
MIT License applies to the package software and does not replace those terms.
See inst/COPYRIGHTS for a concise installed-package notice.

